        "title": "Process Management Solution",
        "body": "<p>I'm working on a project that requires a process management solution much like init.d but with the following requirements:<\/p>\n\n<p>1) Working with Windows not Linux\n2) Must be able to start/stop/restart programs written in heterogeneous languages.\n3) Must be able to extend process manager to start / stop processes depending on run-mode information obtained from remote-host over pub/sub interface (most likely DDS).<\/p>\n\n<p>Ideally we would want this in Java, but can be C / C++. Also, the process manager must be fail safe (I assume running in a service with auto-restart on fail will be enough).<\/p>\n\n<p>I could write my own implementation for scratch, but we have a unreasonably tight schedule, so obviously an already developed solution is preferable.<\/p>\n\n<p>Michael<\/p>\n",
